n,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## File 2: `pkg/controller/istiocsr/deployments.go`\n\nAdd the `--tls-min-version` flag to the argument list when the field is set.\n\n### Change — Add `--tls-min-version` flag in `updateArgList`\n\n**Before** (lines 173-178):\n```go\n\t// Add configmap-namespace-selector argument if configured\n\tif istiocsrConfigs.IstioDataPlaneNamespaceSelector != \"\" {\n\t\targs = append(args, fmt.Sprintf(\"--configmap-namespace-selector=%s\", istiocsrConfigs.IstioDataPlaneNamespaceSelector))\n\t}\n```\n\n**After:**\n```go\n\t// Add configmap-namespace-selector argument if configured\n\tif istiocsrConfigs.IstioDataPlaneNamespaceSelector != \"\" {\n\t\targs = append(args, fmt.Sprintf(\"--configmap-namespace-selector=%s\", istiocsrConfigs.IstioDataPlaneNamespaceSelector))\n\t}\n\n\t// Add tls-min-version argument if configured\n\tif istiocsrConfigs.TLSMinVersion != \"\" {\n\t\targs = append(args, fmt.Sprintf(\"--tls-min-version=%s\", istiocsrConfigs.TLSMinVersion))\n\t}\n```\n\n---\n\n## File 3: `api/operator/v1alpha1/zz_generated.deepcopy.go` (auto-generated)\n\nThis file will be regenerated by `make update`. No manual changes needed — `TLSMinVersion` is a `string`, which is a value type and requires no special deepcopy logic (it's already handled by the `*out = *in` at line 366).\n\n---\n\n## Commands to run (in order)\n\n```bash\n# 1. Regenerate deepcopy functions and CRD manifests\nmake update\n\n# 2. Run unit tests to verify nothing is broken\nmake test\n```\n\n`make update` runs `generate` (controller-gen deepcopy) then `update-manifests` (CRD YAML regeneration) and `update-bindata`, which covers everything needed.\n\n---\n\n## Summary of the design\n\n1. **Presence-immutability** (`IstioCSRConfig` type-level CEL rule): Uses the same pattern as `privateKeyAlgorithm` on `IstiodTLSConfig` (line 180) — `!has(oldSelf.tlsMinVersion) && !has(self.tlsMinVersion) || has(oldSelf.tlsMinVersion) && has(self.tlsMinVersion)`. This prevents adding the fie